<table width="640" align="center">
  <tr>
    <td><p class="style4">It would be nice if we lived in a world where everyone was honest, but unfortunately that is not the case. In fact, the food service industry loses approximately 20 billion dollars a year to theft and 35% of all restaurants fail because of theft. The most common forms of theft in the restaurant are employee (or internal) theft and customer or purveyor (external) theft. While both may be common, solid systems and constant awareness will help to minimize loss.</p>
    </td>
