      <td width="109" valign="top"><img src="../../../images/robbery/gunman.JPG" width="125" height="95" align="top"></td>
      <td width="519"><p align="center" class="style8">Armed Robbery </p>
      <p align="left"><span class="style4">Thank goodness this is the rarest form of theft encountered at Shari's, however, when it happens the effects can be devastating to the crew and guests alike. This type of theft usually happens very quickly with very little time to think of how to react. So, preparing yourself and your employees on what to do in case of robbery is an absolute. While prevention is always best it is important to also discuss what to do during and after the robbery should one occur. The following information was provided by the Colorado Association of Robbery Investigators: </span></p>
      <p align="left"><span class="style5">Prevention - </span></p>
      <ul class="style4">
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4" align="left">Keep your front doors and windows clear of signs and posters to allow good, two way visibility. Employees can see suspicious persons outside. Passers-by and police can see inside. </span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Keep the outside of your business well lit at night. </span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Make sure your cash register area is clearly visible in your establishment.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Practice good cash control. Keep a minimum amount of cash in the register and make regular till pulls.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Don't keep large bills under the cash register drawer. Transfer them to the safe immediately.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Use video camera surveillance and make it well known.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Always have at least two employees working at all times.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Vary your banking routine. Carry cash in a variety of ways - a paper sack, brief case, purse, etc. Money bags are pretty obvious.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Vary the times and routes that you use to go to the bank.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Make deposits daily, before 11:00 a.m. </span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Be alert for &quot;customers&quot; who seem to be loitering or glancing around the store and not wanting to be seated.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Watch for suspicious persons outside the building - especially parked cars for lengthy periods of time.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">If you see someone who is acting suspicious inside or outside, call the police to have them checked out.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Two persons should be on hand when removing trash from the building after dark.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Keep side and back doors locked. Have employees use the main entrance to enter and exit the building.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Place markers at the main entrance that employees can use to gauge the height of a robber if he leaves. </span></div>
        </li>
        </ul>
      <p><strong>During The Robbery -</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4" align="left">Try to stay calm. Don't make any sudden movements to upset the robber. </span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Do exactly as you are told. <em>DO NOT RESIST! </em></span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">If you have an alarm, activate it only if you can do it secretly.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Tell the robber about anything that might surprise him, such as someone who may walk out of a back room etc.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">If you move or reach, tell the robber what you are going to do and why.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Try to get a good look at the robber so you can describe him later.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Don't be a hero. It's better to lose your money than your life or the lives of others.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Give the robber time to leave before calling the police.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Note his direction of travel when he leaves.</span></div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div align="left"><span class="style4">Try to get a description of his vehicle <em>ONLY </em>if you can do so without exposing yourself to harm. </span></div>
        </li>
        </ul>
      <p><strong>After The Robbery -</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li class="style4">
          <div align="left">Call the police immediately, even of you have already activated an alarm.</div>
        </li>
        <li class="style4">
          <div align="left">Close the store and lock the door(s). </div>
        </li>
        <li class="style4">
          <div align="left">Do not discuss the details of the robbery with witnesses or fellow employees.</div>
        </li>
        <li class="style4">
          <div align="left">Ask witnesses to stay until the police arrive. If they can't, get their names, phone numbers and addresses.</div>
        </li>
        <li class="style4">
          <div align="left">Do not touch anything that the robber may have touched. Block off areas where the robber was if necessary.</div>
        </li>
        <li class="style4">
          <div align="left">Try to recall as much as you can about the robber's appearance, speech and mannerisms.</div>
        </li>
        <li class="style4">
          <div align="left">Stay on the phone with the 911 operator until the police arrive or the operator terminates the call.</div>
        </li>
        <li class="style4">
          <div align="left">Let the police answer inquiries from the news media.</div>
        </li>
        <li class="style4">
          <div align="left">Do not discuss the amount of money taken with anyone other than the police and your supervisor.</div>
        </li>
        </ul>
      <p><strong>Shari's Robbery Policy -</strong></p>
      <p align="left"><span class="style4">It is Shari's policy that you cooperate with the robber. The safety of you, your crew and guests is the top priority! </span></p>
      <div align="left">
        <ul>
            <li><span class="style4">Remain calm.</span></li>
            <li><span class="style4">Be cooperative. Remember that money can be replaced, lives cannot.</span></li>
            <li><span class="style4">Explain your movements very slowly.</span></li>
            <li><span class="style4">Make mental notes about the physical characteristics of the robber.</span></li>
            <li><span class="style4">Do not disturb evidence.</span></li>
            <li><span class="style4">Do not attempt to follow the robber into the parking lot or confront them in any way.</span></li>
            <li><span class="style4">Call 911.</span></li>
            <li><span class="style4">Check on guests and crew to make sure all are safe and okay.</span></li>
            <li><span class="style4">Begin making contacts. Your General and District Managers need notification as well as the Regional Vice President.</span></li>
            <li><span class="style4">Handout &quot;Crime Suspect Description Forms&quot; to any witnesses. They are located in the Robbery Chapter of the Emergency Situations Binder.</span></li>
            <li><span class="style4">Make an entry in the manager's log regarding the incident.</span></li>
        </ul>
        <p class="style4">We hope you and your crew never have to face this horrible situation, however keep in mind, armed robbers usually want in and out as quickly as possible leaving you little time to think or plan. Have your plan set firm in your mind and train your crew to be as prepared as possible should they be faced with a person with a gun demanding money. </p>
        <p class="style4">&nbsp;</p>
      </div>      
      </td>
    </tr>
